Description:
COMPANY PROFILE
Lakson International Development is a Montreal-based engineering company that specializes in the design and development of new technological processes for use in green, renewable and alternative energy projects. Lakson’s solutions include:
the valorization of biomass for thermal use, for fertilizer production, or other;
the conditioning of municipal and industrial sludges for waste reduction and valorization purposes;
agri-food processing for the production of high-value food derivatives;
treatment of wastewater effluents;
biomass combustion and integration of related systems for the production of heat, steam and electricity (boilers, dryers, furnaces, cogeneration plants).
JOB DESCRIPTION
Lakson International Development is currently looking for a young graduate in engineering with strong skills in computer-aided design, design and manufacturing, to join its team, part-time or full-time (to be discussed).
Main Responsabilities
Produce layout plans for industrial projects;
Produce process flow diagrams (PFD) and piping and instrumentation diagrams (P&ID);
Participate in the (3D) design of technological machines;
Produce detail, fabrication and assembly drawings, as well as lists of materials;
Visit fabrication sub-contractors to ensure conformity with drawings;
Search for fabrication sub-contractors, obtain quotations and manage communications;
Search for equipment suppliers, obtain quotations and manage communications.
Requirements and Skills
University degree in engineering, preferably mechanical engineering with a specialization in design;
From 0 to 4 years of experience in drafting and computer-aided design;
Having great organization skills and attention to details;
Being autonomous and being able to work well under pressure;
Having great interpersonal and communication skills;
Mastering Autocad;
Mastering Inventor;
Mastering Microsoft Office software;
Fluent in English;
Proficient in French (an asset).
Other languages are assets.
